  Read more
  <span class="sr-only">about our new product launch</span>
</a>

<button>
  <svg aria-hidden="true">
    <use href="#icon-delete"></use>
  </svg>
  <span class="sr-only">Delete item</span>
</button>

<style>
/* ‚úÖ Good: Screen reader only class */
.sr-only {
  position: absolute;
  width: 1px;
  height: 1px;
  padding: 0;
  margin: -1px;
  overflow: hidden;
  clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0);
  white-space: nowrap;
  border-width: 0;
}

/* Show on focus for keyboard users */
.sr-only:focus {
  position: static;
  width: auto;
  height: auto;
  padding: inherit;
  margin: inherit;
  overflow: visible;
  clip: auto;
  white-space: normal;
}
</style>
```

## ‚ùå DON'T (Anti-patterns)

### Semantic HTML Mistakes
- ‚ùå **Div/span for buttons/links**: Not accessible
- ‚ùå **Skipping heading levels**: h1 ‚Üí h3 (skip h2)
- ‚ùå **Multiple h1 per page**: Confuses hierarchy
- ‚ùå **Tables for layout**: Use CSS Grid/Flexbox

### ARIA Mistakes
- ‚ùå **Overusing ARIA**: Use native HTML first
- ‚ùå **Conflicting roles**: Don't override native semantics
- ‚ùå **Incorrect relationships**: aria-labelledby pointing to non-existent ID
- ‚ùå **Missing required attributes**: role="button" without tabindex

### Keyboard Mistakes
- ‚ùå **Removing focus indicators**: Never `outline: none` without alternative
- ‚ùå **Non-focusable interactives**: Div buttons without tabindex
- ‚ùå **Focus traps**: Can't escape modal/dropdown
- ‚ùå **Illogical tab order**: Using tabindex > 0

### Content Mistakes
- ‚ùå **Missing alt text**: Empty or missing alt attributes
- ‚ùå **Color-only information**: "Click the red button"
- ‚ùå **Auto-playing media**: Without controls or way to stop
- ‚ùå **Time limits**: Without way to extend or disable

## üìù Accessibility Checklist

Before launching, verify:
- [ ] All images have appropriate alt text
- [ ] Color contrast meets WCAG AA (4.5:1 for text)
- [ ] All functionality available via keyboard
- [ ] Focus indicators are clearly visible
- [ ] Proper heading hierarchy (h1 ‚Üí h2 ‚Üí h3)
- [ ] Form inputs have explicit labels
- [ ] Error messages are clear and associated with fields
- [ ] ARIA labels where needed (icons, custom controls)
- [ ] Videos have captions/transcripts
- [ ] Page has descriptive `<title>`
- [ ] Language is declared (`<html lang="en">`)
- [ ] Skip links for keyboard users
- [ ] Responsive text (zoom to 200%)
- [ ] Tested with screen reader (NVDA, JAWS, VoiceOver)
- [ ] No keyboard traps

## üìä WCAG Compliance Levels

| Level | Description | Requirements |
|-------|-------------|--------------|
| **A** | Minimum | Essential accessibility features |
| **AA** | Recommended | Standard for most sites (legal requirement) |
| **AAA** | Optimal | Enhanced accessibility (not always possible) |

**Target**: WCAG **2.2** Level **AA** compliance minimum (2.1 AA as baseline where needed)

## üìù Key Points

### Must Have
- Semantic HTML elements
- Keyboard accessibility for all interactions
- Sufficient color contrast (4.5:1 minimum)
- Alt text for all meaningful images
- Explicit form labels
- Visible focus indicators
- ARIA where native HTML insufficient

### Do
- Use native HTML elements first
- Test with keyboard only
- Test with screen readers
- Provide multiple ways to access content
- Use clear, plain language
- Provide text alternatives for media
- Maintain logical heading hierarchy
- Include skip links

### Don't
- Don't use div/span for buttons/links
- Don't remove focus indicators without replacement
- Don't rely on color alone
- Don't auto-play videos/audio
- Don't use ARIA when native HTML works
- Don't skip heading levels
- Don't forget alt text
- Don't create keyboard traps

